## Supabase details

- Production is on Supabase free tier (org ID: xfgtjrilgugxlqsczqdp).
- **Local development uses a local Supabase stack** via `supabase start` (Docker). Run `pnpm db:start` before `pnpm dev`.
  - `.env.development.local` points to the local instance (auto-loaded by `next dev`).
  - `.env.local` keeps production credentials (used by `next build` and Vercel).
  - Local Supabase Studio: http://127.0.0.1:54323
- To refresh local data from production: `supabase db dump --linked -f production_dump.sql && supabase db dump --linked --data-only -f production_data.sql`, then restore with `psql`.
- Supabase has a limit of 1000 when presenting results sometimes. When making queries we need to handle this as if results can be way more than that hard limit, using pagination perhaps.
